{"title":"QuikrStuff Mach2 Hitch Rack Adds or Removes Bikes in Seconds","link":"https://bikerumor.com/quikrstuff-hitch-bike-rack/","date":1780086900000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-2-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"QuikrStuff hitch bike rack with mountain bike rolling onto it.\" /></p>\n<p>The QuikrStuff Mach 2 hitch rack popped on our radar via <a href=\"https://adventurouswayoflife.com/overland-digest-25/\" target=\"_blank\">AWOL’s Overland Digest</a>, and it’s interesting in several ways. This new LV (literally “Longer Version”) just launched with a longer stinger to help it clear bumpers, tailgates, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For starters, there’s the eerie similarity to 1UP USA’s racks. And that’s because QuikrStuff’s founder Cal Phillips originally founded 1UP USA with the Quik Rack, too. He sold that company, and after the original patents expired, he got back in the game to bring a few new ideas to market.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Where 1UP has branched out into heavy duty racks for motos, overland gear mounts, QuikrStuff is (for now anyway) focused on bicycles. Their single model, the Mach2, starts with a 1-bike Single Rack base.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, you can by Add-Ons to increase capacity up to four bikes, but the trick is in how they attach.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4.jpg\"><img width=\"1586\" height=\"1136\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4.jpg\" alt=\"closeup of mounting add-on bike tray on QuikrStuff hitch bike rack.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4.jpg 1586w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4-297x213.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4-1536x1100.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4-120x86.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4-768x550.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-4-1257x900.jpg 1257w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you skipped the video above, here’s how it works:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Unbox and install base rack</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click Add-On into place</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Load bikes</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"693\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"closeup of add-on tray mounting system on QuikrStuff hitch bike rack.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-297x80.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-1536x416.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-120x32.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-768x208.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-2048x554.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-add-on-hitch-bike-rack-mounting-details-1600x433.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Installing each Add-On takes just five seconds and zero tools. It’s just as easy to remove, simply hold the release lever that locks it into place, tilt it up, and pull it off. Even better, each Add-On has a release lever, so you never have to reach all the way under the rack to tilt it up.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3.jpg\"><img width=\"1200\" height=\"799\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3.jpg\" alt=\"QuikrStuff hitch bike rack tilting down to open truck bed.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3-768x511.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It tilts down, too, letting you drop it down to access the back of your vehicle. And the whole thing folds up to the size of a small carry-on suitcase, making it easy to stow in your trunk or garage when not in use.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5.jpg\"><img width=\"1080\" height=\"718\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5.jpg\" alt=\"rider locking bike onto QuikrStuff hitch bike rack.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5.jpg 1080w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5-297x197.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5-768x511.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-5-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new LV model has a total weight rating of 165lbs, but actual max capacity depends on your configuration:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>1 bike –   75 pounds</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 bikes – 130 pounds total</li>\n\n\n\n<li>3 bikes – 165 pounds total</li>\n\n\n\n<li>4 bikes – 105 pounds total</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6.jpg\"><img width=\"1277\" height=\"850\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6.jpg\" alt=\"lady rolling e-bike onto QuikrStuff hitch bike rack using integrated ramp.\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6.jpg 1277w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6-768x511.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/quikrstuff-modular-hitch-bike-rack-6-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For e-bike users, there’s also a quick-add Ramp that attaches to the rear of the rack in the same way. This makes it super easy to transport without having to shove it in your vehicle (or create manufacturing complexity by trying to slide it into the rack).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>QuikrStuff Mach2 LV Specs &amp; Weights:</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Weight: 30.9 pounds</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shipping weight: 35.2 pounds</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tray length: 56.3″</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Folded size: 28-½” x 17-¾” x 7-¾”</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shipping dimensions: 31”x19”x9”</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Base racks range from $799 to $879 and come in 2″ and 1.25″ versions. Add-Ons are $699 each, ramps are $299. Options include wheel locks, wheel straps, cable locks, license plate mount, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://quikrstuff.com\" target=\"_blank\">QuikrStuff.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/quikrstuff-hitch-bike-rack/\">QuikrStuff Mach2 Hitch Rack Adds or Removes Bikes in Seconds</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Staff","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"cc01298f1cc7a327f145e1ea2b9c8b80ba5dccd4772b68731acaf9b115942b78","category":"Cycling"}